text.tspan: Selected vias are to be plugged with a secondary mask print on the top surface.
Gerber file is layout.via_plugs.gbr. Plugging is to be done after ENIG finish. Maximum height
of plugs above surrounding pad 2 mils. Plug height to be as uniform as possible.
Use soldermask layers as drawn; no additional clearance should be applied
No ink on pads or vias
Thieving: allowed on outer layers only; allowed to within 100 mils of any copper feature
UL logo, manufacturer's logo, manufacturer's part identification, 94V rating, and date code
shall be rendered in copper on the bottom side of the board in an unobtrusive place well clear
All material must be RoHS compliant
Most vias are encroached. The soldermask clearance aims to avoid tenting
